//=============================================================================
// Michelle_GMMA — Guppy Multiple Moving Average (GMMA)
//=============================================================================
// 
// 12 EMAs plotted on the price panel, divided into two color groups:
//   • P1–P6  (short-term / "traders" group)   — ORANGE  (#FF8D1E)
//   • P7–P12 (long-term  / "investors" group) — CYAN    (#13FFFF)
//
// Default periods (standard Guppy GMMA values):
//   P1=3,  P2=5,  P3=8,  P4=10, P5=12, P6=15
//   P7=30, P8=35, P9=40, P10=45, P11=50, P12=60
//
// Default visibility: ALL ENABLED EXCEPT P7 and P9 (matches Michelle's chart style).
// Users can toggle any EMA on/off and change any period in the indicator settings.
//
//-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
// HOW TO CHANGE HARDCODED VALUES
//-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
//
// 1) LINE THICKNESS (currently 1 = thin)
//    In State.SetDefaults, find the 12 "AddPlot(new Stroke(...))" lines.
//    Change the "1" in "new Stroke(brush, 1)" to 2, 3, etc. for thicker lines.
//    Example: new Stroke(orange, 1)  →  new Stroke(orange, 2)
//
// 2) COLORS
//    In State.SetDefaults, the two Brush variables at the top:
//        Brush orange = ... ;  // currently #FF8D1E
//        Brush cyan   = ... ;  // currently #13FFFF
//    Change the hex codes inside Color.FromRgb(...) to use different colors.
//    Or use any built-in brush like Brushes.Yellow, Brushes.Magenta, etc.
//
// 3) CALCULATION MODE (currently OnBarClose)
//    In State.SetDefaults: Calculate = Calculate.OnBarClose;
//    Change to Calculate.OnEachTick for real-time intraday updates,
//    or Calculate.OnPriceChange for updates on every price change.
//
// 4) DEFAULT PERIOD VALUES
//    Scroll to the Properties region at the bottom. Each property looks like:
//        public int P1 { get; set; }
//    The default value is set in State.SetDefaults (e.g. P1 = 3;).
//    Change those numbers to use different default periods.
//
// 5) DEFAULT VISIBILITY (which EMAs are checked on by default)
//    In State.SetDefaults, find the "Show_P1 = true;" lines.
//    Change true ↔ false to flip the default checkbox state for each EMA.
//
// 6) PANEL (currently overlay on price panel)
//    IsOverlay = true; means EMAs plot on the price chart.
//    Change to false to put them in a separate sub-pane (unusual for GMMA).
//
//=============================================================================

